DISCOVER-codec - Software for Distributed Video Coding

This software is called DISCOVER-codec and is the copyrighted work of the research
project "Distributed coding for video services" (DISCOVER), FP6-2002-IST-C contract
no.: 015314 of the European Commission. It cannot be copied, reproduced nor
distributed without the consent of the project consortium.

  1) The DISCOVER software started from the so-called IST-WZ software developed at
     the Image Group from Instituto Superior Técnico (IST), Lisbon-Portugal
     (http://amalia.img.lx.it.pt/), by Catarina Brites, João Ascenso, and Fernando
     Pereira.
  2) Portions of the IST-WZ software are based on the work of Mathys Walma, which is
     free to use for academic and personal purposes only (walma@sce.carleton.ca).
     These portions are identified in the IST-WZ and DISCOVER softwares.
  3) Portions of the DISCOVER-codec are based on David Varadoyan's (varodayan@stanford.edu),
     code taken from http://www.stanford.edu/~divad/software.html.

For more information see the official DISCOVER web site (http://www.discoverdvc.org)
and contact the project coordinator Luis Torres (luis@gps.tsc.upc.edu).


